  "text": "The Envoy dynamic cluster discovery and health checking implementation is distributed across several key components:\n\n## CDS (Cluster Discovery Service) Subscription\nCluster discovery is managed through three main components in envoyproxy/envoy:\n\n1. **CdsApiImpl** (source/common/upstream/cds_api_impl.cc/h) - The main CDS subscription implementation that extends Config::SubscriptionBase<Cluster>. It handles cluster resource subscription, configuration updates via onConfigUpdate(), and failure handling via onConfigUpdateFailed().\n\n2. **CdsApiHelper** (source/common/upstream/cds_api_helper.cc/h) - A helper class that processes CDS configuration updates and notifies the cluster manager of cluster additions and removals.\n\n3. **OdCdsApiImpl** (source/common/upstream/od_cds_api_impl.cc/h) - On-demand CDS implementation that lazily fetches clusters as needed, with methods like updateOnDemand().\n\n4. **ClusterDiscoveryManager** (source/common/upstream/cluster_discovery_manager.cc/h) - Thread-local on-demand cluster discovery manager that invokes discovery callbacks and manages cluster lifecycle callbacks.\n\n## Cluster Manager Update Logic\nThe cluster manager handles dynamic cluster updates through:\n\n1. **ClusterManagerImpl** (source/common/upstream/cluster_manager_impl.cc/h) - The main cluster manager implementation with critical methods:\n   - addOrUpdateCluster() - Adds or updates clusters, managing warming vs. active cluster states\n   - loadCluster() - Creates cluster instances with proper initialization\n   - removeCluster() - Removes dynamically added clusters\n\n2. **ClusterManagerInitHelper** (source/common/upstream/cluster_manager_impl.h) - Manages the complex initialization state machine for primary clusters, secondary clusters, and CDS-populated clusters, with states: Loading, WaitingForPrimaryInitializationToComplete, WaitingToStartSecondaryInitialization, WaitingToStartCdsInitialization, CdsInitialized, and AllClustersInitialized.\n\n3. **ClusterFactoryImplBase** (source/common/upstream/cluster_factory_impl.cc/h) - Factory for creating cluster instances from protobuf configurations, coordinating with the outlier detection and health checking subsystems.\n\n4. **ClusterUpdateTracker** (source/common/upstream/cluster_update_tracker.cc/h) - Tracks cluster updates and manages the warming-to-active cluster transition.\n\n## Cluster Implementation\nThe base cluster implementation in **upstream_impl.cc/h** contains:\n- ClusterImplBase - Base class for all cluster implementations with initialization hooks\n- HostDescriptionImplBase - Host/endpoint representation with health checker and outlier detector integration\n- Integration points for health checking via setHealthChecker() and setOutlierDetector()\n\n## Active Health Check Scheduling\nHealth checking is implemented across multiple components:\n\n1. **Core Health Checking** (source/common/upstream/):\n   - **HealthCheckerImpl** (health_checker_impl.cc/h) - Factory and base implementation for health checkers\n   - **HealthCheckerFactory::create()** - Creates appropriate health checker based on configuration\n   - **HealthDiscoveryService** (health_discovery_service.cc/h) - Service for health discovery subscriptions\n   - **HealthCheckerEventLogger** (health_checker_event_logger.cc/h) - Logs health check events\n\n2. **Health Checker Implementations** (source/extensions/health_checkers/):\n   - **HealthCheckerBaseImpl** (common/health_checker_base_impl.cc/h) - Base implementation with interval scheduling\n   - **HttpHealthCheckerImpl** (http/health_checker_impl.cc/h) - HTTP health checking with interval-based probing via onInterval()\n   - **GrpcHealthCheckerImpl** (grpc/health_checker_impl.cc/h) - gRPC health checking using gRPC.Health.v1 service\n   - **TcpHealthCheckerImpl** (tcp/health_checker_impl.cc/h) - TCP health checking with payload matching\n   - **RedisHealthChecker** (redis/redis.cc/h) - Redis protocol health checking\n   - **ThriftHealthChecker** (thrift/thrift.cc/h) - Thrift protocol health checking\n\nHealth checks are scheduled through Event::Dispatcher timers set at intervals defined in HealthCheck configuration protobuf.\n\n## Outlier Detection Integration\nOutlier detection is managed through:\n\n1. **OutlierDetectionImpl** (source/common/upstream/outlier_detection_impl.cc/h) - Main outlier detection implementation with:\n   - DetectorImplFactory::createForCluster() - Factory for creating detectors for clusters\n   - DetectorImpl - Monitors host health metrics and ejects unhealthy hosts\n   - Success rate tracking via SuccessRateAccumulator and SuccessRateMonitor\n   - Event logging for ejection/unejection events\n\n2. **Integration with Clusters** - OutlierDetectorHostMonitor is integrated into HostDescriptionImplBase via setOutlierDetector(), allowing real-time health metric collection and host ejection.\n\n## Cluster Type Implementations\nVarious cluster implementations handle discovery:\n- **EDS Cluster** (source/extensions/clusters/eds/eds.cc/h) - Endpoint Discovery Service for dynamic endpoint updates\n- **StrictDNS** (source/extensions/clusters/strict_dns/) - DNS-based cluster resolution\n- **LogicalDNS** (source/extensions/clusters/logical_dns/) - Single endpoint DNS cluster\n- **StaticCluster** (source/extensions/clusters/static/) - Statically configured clusters\n- **AggregateCluster** (source/extensions/clusters/aggregate/) - Composite cluster combining multiple clusters\n\n## Data Flow\nThe complete flow: CDS subscription (CdsApiImpl) → CdsApiHelper notifies ClusterManager → ClusterManagerImpl::addOrUpdateCluster() → ClusterFactoryImplBase creates cluster → Cluster initialization triggers HealthCheckerFactory → Health checks scheduled on Event::Dispatcher → OutlierDetectionImpl monitors results → Host ejection/unejection events logged."
}

